user.name: Brandon Smith
user.bio: Life is a canvas.

results.description: One of the most beautiful things I’ve seen in the desert is Antelope Canyons. With its wavy walls, smooth texture and beautiful curves, I began to see the abstract beauty that nature has taken thousands of years to create. Mostly known for their light beams and beautiful colors, I decided to take a monochrome, abstract approach that is rarely seen. This is part 10 of a 10 picture series.
